estoration of male hormones
Without correcting hormone levels to that of a 30-35 year old, you cannot enjoy optimum health and prevent chronic
disease. Many clients with CardioMetabolic disease cannot recover without replacing testosterone, thyroid and other
hormones (BHRT is safe and efective).
Progesterone
helps to counteract the efects of estrogen on the male body. In
addition, men with low levels of progesterone have a higher risk of developing
health conditions, such as osteoporosis, arthritis, prostatism and prostate cancer.
Testosterone
plays a key role in the development of male reproductive
tissues such as the testis and prostate as well as promoting secondary sexual
characteristics such as increased muscle, bone mass, and the growth of body hair.
Estradiol
if the amount of estradiol compared to testosterone increases,certain
symptoms such as weight gain especially in the midsection, development of
enlarged breasts, and decreased sex drive can occur.
DHT
is responsible for the development of all of the male secondary sexual
characteristics like the deepening of the vocal chords, male hair patterns on the
body, hair on the face, oily skin and nally, male sexual drive and function.
Thyroid
blood tests for thyroid are often wrong. It is impossible to lose weight
and have energy if levels are not optimal. (Thyroex is a better diagnostic test
than blood tests for thyroid function)
Cortisol
is released in response to stress, acting to restore homeostasis.
However, prolonged cortisol secretion results in signicant negative p
hysiological
changes.
Insulin
is a hormone, produced by the pancreas, which is central to regulating
carbohydrate, protein and fat metabolism in the body. Without it, the body
cannot control or properly use glucose (sugar) one of its main energy supplying
fuels.
Vitamin D3
plays a role in controlling the immune system increasing neuro-muscular
function, improving mood, and protecting the brain and heart against toxic chemicals.
It is also important for sleep, sugar control and bone health.
IgF
is measured to help diagnose the cause of growth abnormalities, evaluate
pituitary function, and monitor treatment of Growth Hormone deciencies and
excesses. Many consider this an important hormone to combat the efects of aging.
DHEA
regulates the reproductive hormones estrogen and testosterone, and is
important for bone health. DHEA is a neur
oactive steroid and regulates mood.
